Sinopec Chairman Su Shulin Resigns to Take Government Post

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-20T14:26:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/sinopec-chairman-su-shulin-resigns-to-take-government-post-1-.html
China Petroleum & Chemical Corp. (600028) 
Chairman Su Shulin resigned with immediate effect to take up a
new position and Vice Chairman Wang Tianpu will take over his
duties until a replacement is appointed, the company, also known
as Sinopec Corp., said in a statement to the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange today.  Su has been appointed acting governor of  Fujian province ,
the provincial Peopleâ€™s Congress said in a statement on its
website on April 11.  Sinopec will propose to shareholders that Fu Chengyu,
chairman of its parent company, state-owned China Petrochemical
Corp., be appointed a non-executive director, the company said.
Fu, former chairman of Cnooc Ltd., was appointed chairman at
China Petrochemical, also known as Sinopec Group, on April 9.  --Xiao Yu. Editor: Nerys Avery  To contact the reporter on this story:
